Distinguished from 

S. tonkoui

(the only similar species and probably closest known relative; see below) by relatively shorter palpal elements (femur, tibia, bulb; 
Figs 100-101
), by large hooked apophysis on bulb (
Fig. 100
; in 

S. tonkoui

pair of small apophyses distally on long bulb), by shorter proximal frontal apophyses on male chelicerae (
Fig. 103
), and by pair of small pockets in posterior epigynal plate (
Fig. 104
).

